<section id="readingText">
  <p align="left">Dear Hilary,</p>
  <p align="left">I've just finished reading the most amazing book and I just had to write and tell you about it as I <font color="#0000ff">[19] you'd really enjoy it. You've probably heard about these books but won't have read them because they <font color="#0000ff">[20]</font> for children &#x2013; J.K. Rowling's 'Harry Potter' series?</font></p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Well, last night I stayed up all night reading the first in the series &#x2013; 'Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone'. The plot of each book <font color="#0000ff">[21]</font> around a young boy called Harry Potter and his best friends Ron and Hermione. They all <font color="#0000ff">[22]</font> to a school for wizards, which is where most of the story <font color="#0000ff">[23]</font>. In this book Harry <font color="#0000ff">[24]</font> lots of tricks like how to fly a broom and how to use a cloak to make himself invisible and <font color="#0000ff">[25]</font> to go through a series of dangerous trials. My description <font color="#0000ff">[26]</font> the book seem childish but Rowling <font color="#0000ff">[27]</font> a wonderful storyteller and her books <font color="#0000ff">[28]</font> compulsive reading. The characters are amazingly three-dimensional, although I <font color="#0000ff">[30]</font> in this particular book they <font color="#0000ff">[31]</font> to behave a little out of character towards the end in order to serve the plot. However, the books are really quite special and I can't recommend them enough.</font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">Anyway, just give one of the books a go. I know you'll absolutely love them. If you <font color="#0000ff">[34] to splash out on the books yourself, I <font color="#0000ff">[35]</font> them all in hardback and you are welcome to borrow them anytime.</font></p>
  <p align="left">Looking forward to hearing from you soon.</p>
  <p align="left">Lots of love, Janine</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font size="2"/>
  </p>
</section>

